<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1734,2010]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,322,1842,1867]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Comment.</emphasis>
The single male resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[632,801,1843,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Peloridiidae" genus="Xenophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinlochensis">
<emphasis box="[632,801,1843,1867]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">X. kinlochensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the presence of the basally developed vein M of the tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[331,413,1878,1902]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 20" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,204,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 20. Habitus of Xenophyes spp., even numbers 3, odd numbers Ƥ. 6, 7. X. adelphus sp. nov. 8 – 11. X. cascus: 8, 9 — North Island. 10, 11 — South Island. 12, 13. X. goniomus sp. nov. 14, 15. X. kinlochensis. 16, 17. X. metoponcus sp. nov. 18, 19. X. rhachilophus sp. nov. 20. X. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200940/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[384,413,1878,1902]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
) as well as the shape of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[854,948,1878,1902]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 33" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[231,1338,206,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[222,1350,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 33. Xenophyes spp. 21, 27. X. adelphus sp. nov. 22, 28. X. cascus. 23, 29. X. goniomus sp. nov. 24, 30. X. kinlochensis. 25, 31. X. metoponcus sp. nov. 26, 32. X. rhachilophus sp. nov. 33. X. sp. 21 – 26. Head and pronotum. 27 – 33. Male aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200941/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs. 33</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[961,991,1878,1902]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,193,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1405,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 47. Xenophyes spp. 34, 41. X. adelphus sp. nov. 35, 42. X. cascus. 36, 43. X. goniomus sp. nov. 37, 44. X. kinlochensis. 38, 45. X. metoponcus sp. nov. 39, 46. X. rhachilophus sp. nov. 40, 47. X. sp. 34 – 40. Aedeagus, frontal view. 41 – 47. Male paramere, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200942/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">40</figureCitation>
) and pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[1191,1275,1878,1902]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 61" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[198,1381,196,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[188,1385,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 61. Xenophyes spp. 48, 55. X. adelphus sp. nov. 49, 56. X. cascus. 50, 57. X. goniomus sp. nov. 51, 58. X. kinlochensis. 52, 59. X. metoponcus sp. nov. 53, 60. X. rhachilophus sp. nov. 54, 61. X. sp. 48 – 54. Male anal tube, dorsal view. 55 – 61. Male pygophore, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200943/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[1244,1275,1878,1902]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="61.0">61</number>
</figureCitation>
); but it has an oblong-oval body shape, a cross vein in the basal radial cell (
<figureCitation box="[850,935,1914,1938]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 20" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[203,1384,204,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 20. Habitus of Xenophyes spp., even numbers 3, odd numbers Ƥ. 6, 7. X. adelphus sp. nov. 8 – 11. X. cascus: 8, 9 — North Island. 10, 11 — South Island. 12, 13. X. goniomus sp. nov. 14, 15. X. kinlochensis. 16, 17. X. metoponcus sp. nov. 18, 19. X. rhachilophus sp. nov. 20. X. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200940/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[904,935,1914,1938]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
), shorter parameres (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1260,1914,1938]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,193,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[176,1405,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 47. Xenophyes spp. 34, 41. X. adelphus sp. nov. 35, 42. X. cascus. 36, 43. X. goniomus sp. nov. 37, 44. X. kinlochensis. 38, 45. X. metoponcus sp. nov. 39, 46. X. rhachilophus sp. nov. 40, 47. X. sp. 34 – 40. Aedeagus, frontal view. 41 – 47. Male paramere, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200942/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[1229,1260,1914,1938]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="47.0">47</number>
</figureCitation>
), and a slightly more slender male anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[480,564,1950,1974]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 61" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[198,1381,196,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[188,1385,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 61. Xenophyes spp. 48, 55. X. adelphus sp. nov. 49, 56. X. cascus. 50, 57. X. goniomus sp. nov. 51, 58. X. kinlochensis. 52, 59. X. metoponcus sp. nov. 53, 60. X. rhachilophus sp. nov. 54, 61. X. sp. 48 – 54. Male anal tube, dorsal view. 55 – 61. Male pygophore, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200943/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[532,564,1950,1974]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
). More material is needed to elucidate the identity of this specimen and that of the nymph from Bald Hill whose association with the male is provisional.
</paragraph>
